# name: test_command_help_matches_snapshot[config_set]
  '''
  
   Usage: assembly config set [OPTIONS]
   KEY:{active_profile|env|telemetry_enabled}
                              VALUE
  
   Change one setting (`env` writes to the selected profile).
  
  ╭─ Arguments ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │ *    key        KEY:{active_profile|env|tele  Which setting to change.       │
  │                 metry_enabled}                [required]                     │
  │ *    value      TEXT                          The new value. [required]      │
  ╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
  ╭─ Options ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │ --json  -j        Output raw JSON.                                           │
  │ --help            Show this message and exit.                                │
  ╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
  
   Examples
   Switch the default profile
   $ assembly config set active_profile staging
   Bind the active profile to the sandbox
   $ assembly config set env sandbox000
   Opt out of telemetry
   $ assembly config set telemetry_enabled false
  
  
  
  '''
